      <bioghist id="ref2">
         <head>Biographical Sketch</head>
         <p>1869-1962 Frank Morton Jones Frank was a 20th century naturalist, investigating primarily entomology, particularly Lepidoptera and the insects associated with the pitcher plant family Sarraceniaceae. In 1954 Frank Morton Jones donated a bulk of his library, archival material, and collection to the Yale Peabody Museum.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="ref4">
         <head>Description of the Material</head>
         <p>The Archives of Frank Morton Jones were donated to the Yale Peabody Museum in 1954.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
